{"id": 1997, "title": "Ticket #1997: init script should create /var/run/condor", "description": "<blockquote>\nDuring 'start', the init script should create $RUN if it doesn't exist.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2011-Mar-24 20:09:40 by bbockelm:</em> <br/>\n\nThis seems like the wrong thing to do in RHEL-world.\n\n<p>/var/run/condor should be created and owned by the Condor RPM.\n\n</p><p>Brian\n\n</p><p></p><hr/>\n<em>2011-Mar-24 21:06:19 by nleroy:</em> <br/>\n\nBrian,\n\n<p>I think that as I updated it, it'll do The Right Thing(TM).  Basically, if <code>/var/run/condor</code> already exists (aka it was created by the RPM), it'll do nothing.  If it doesn't exist, however, it'll create it and fix it's ownership.\n\n</p><p>Hopefully that should satisfy your worries.\n\n</p><p>-Nick</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=2081\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('2081'); return false;\" title=\"rpm init / boot script bugs related to status and shutdown requests\">#2081</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nrpm init / boot script bugs related to status and shutdown requests</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2011-Mar-24 17:23</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/7fa87157c61ce39be6f65523a0d46817c175b580\">[21149]</a></span>: One last review patch for <span class=\"ticket\